    # "A true smile, one imbued with all the love he had for her, and she received with all the love she had for him."
    ""

# SailorPath10_1137fc91 (line 34614)
translate ru SailorPath10_1137fc91:
    # "In the weeks that followed, Sarah felt her body slowly recover from the terrors of childbirth."
    ""

# SailorPath10_77a3e778 (line 34615)
translate ru SailorPath10_77a3e778:
    # "Even her insatiable husband seemed to hold off for some time."
    ""

# SailorPath10_96e5809e (line 34616)
translate ru SailorPath10_96e5809e:
    # "Whenever he looked at her, Sarah noticed something appeared to have changed."
    ""

# SailorPath10_166d0b03 (line 34617)
translate ru SailorPath10_166d0b03:
    # "Out of the many ways that he had looked at her, never had he looked at her with respect."
    ""

# SailorPath10_675b8aaf (line 34618)
translate ru SailorPath10_675b8aaf:
    # "Perhaps, she concluded, having delivered him a firstborn and having seen what she went through, he now had a different estimation of her."
    ""

# SailorPath10_4a4120b0 (line 34619)
translate ru SailorPath10_4a4120b0:
    # "Whatever it was, it changed little regarding how he treated her."
    ""

# SailorPath10_9ea0aca1 (line 34620)
translate ru SailorPath10_9ea0aca1:
    # "As soon as her body had healed, he began to take her as he always had. Sarah found herself grateful for it."
    ""

# SailorPath10_2d2f325c (line 34621)
translate ru SailorPath10_2d2f325c:
    # "With the matter of a child now settled, Sarah found her husband using her in ways that were less suitable for progeny."
    ""

# SailorPath10_e4eeb322 (line 34622)
translate ru SailorPath10_e4eeb322:
    # "Her mouth, her ass, spilling his seeds across her face."
    ""

# SailorPath10_ff496bb1 (line 34623)
translate ru SailorPath10_ff496bb1:
    # "But Sarah was only glad. Glad that he still desired her for more than just her womb."
    ""

# SailorPath10_fab5425e (line 34624)
translate ru SailorPath10_fab5425e:
    # "Regardless of how they did it, the frequency with which he took her made further pregnancies a matter of time."
    ""

# SailorPath10_cec89441 (line 34625)
translate ru SailorPath10_cec89441:
    # "Before long, Sarah found herself pregnant with a second child."
    ""

# SailorPath10_116e9447 (line 34626)
translate ru SailorPath10_116e9447:
    # "Now burdened with raising his children, Sarah could manage his absences more easily. Loneliness was rarely a factor in a house now overflowing with life and energy."
    ""

# SailorPath10_c10aca45 (line 34627)
translate ru SailorPath10_c10aca45:
    # "Sarah found herself taking to motherhood in a way that felt both natural and easy to her."
    ""

# SailorPath10_87de1653 (line 34628)
translate ru SailorPath10_87de1653:
    # "The many books she'd read, the many teachers she had back in Castle Reinmeer, all that knowledge she used to raise her own."
    ""

# SailorPath10_7ba6e073 (line 34629)
translate ru SailorPath10_7ba6e073:
    # "She decided to keep her origin a secret, even from her own husband and children."
    ""

# SailorPath10_f6c604af (line 34630)
translate ru SailorPath10_f6c604af:
    # "In the end though, Sarah did not feel like she was lying. That life of a princess now felt so alien and removed from her, that it seemed like it belonged to someone else."
    ""

# SailorPath10_d2baf6ff (line 34631)
translate ru SailorPath10_d2baf6ff:
    # "For a few years, this was their rhythm."
    ""

# SailorPath10_4da85d69 (line 34632)
translate ru SailorPath10_4da85d69:
    # "Sarah bore his children, raised them in his absence. They would oscillate between periods where he was away at sea and where he was back on land."
    ""

# SailorPath10_9e2b040e (line 34633)
translate ru SailorPath10_9e2b040e:
    # "When he was away, she felt herself a mother. When he was home, a wife."
    ""

# SailorPath10_2356ca40 (line 34634)
translate ru SailorPath10_2356ca40:
    # "It was some six years, and by now mother to three children, when Sarah watched her husband return one last time."
    ""

# SailorPath10_7da8e725 (line 34635)
translate ru SailorPath10_7da8e725:
    # "Belmont had ran into pirates and escaped only barely."
    ""

# SailorPath10_1537ad8f (line 34636)
translate ru SailorPath10_1537ad8f:
    # "Realizing that his age had finally caught up to him, Belmont decided to sell his ship and retire, in no small part based on the urging of his wife."
    ""

# SailorPath10_744bbc14 (line 34637)
translate ru SailorPath10_744bbc14:
    # "The ship itself was in good condition, fetching them a large sum of money."
    ""

# SailorPath10_f43a4d94 (line 34638)
translate ru SailorPath10_f43a4d94:
    # "It was no fortune that would buy her a castle, but Sarah no longer dreamed of castles."
    ""

# SailorPath10_7974482a (line 34639)
translate ru SailorPath10_7974482a:
    # "It was however enough for her husband to stop working and make sure they would be provided for."
    ""

# SailorPath10_62598631 (line 34640)
translate ru SailorPath10_62598631:
    # "Sarah delighted at having her husband return to her, now without intermissions."
    ""

# SailorPath10_88b00cab (line 34641)
translate ru SailorPath10_88b00cab:
    # "Belmont, for his part, struggled with the reality of his own aging."
    ""

# SailorPath10_e65a3799 (line 34642)
translate ru SailorPath10_e65a3799:
    # "As if hoping to prove himself still a man, he took towards fucking his younger wife."
    ""

# SailorPath10_2b6dfdcd (line 34643)
translate ru SailorPath10_2b6dfdcd:
    # "Sarah knew he struggled, and bore his advances no matter how frequent they became."
    ""

# SailorPath10_203a0bde (line 34644)
translate ru SailorPath10_203a0bde:
    # "In time, she felt her husband settle down into retired life."
    ""

# SailorPath10_4cfbc3bd (line 34645)
translate ru SailorPath10_4cfbc3bd:
    # "He still took her frequently, but such was his nature, it had now simply ceased to be an obsession."
    ""

# SailorPath10_424a56d9 (line 34646)
translate ru SailorPath10_424a56d9:
    # "Instead, to Sarah's surprise, she found her husband taking towards his role as a father."
    ""

# SailorPath10_adbf9b68 (line 34647)
translate ru SailorPath10_adbf9b68:
    # "She had seen many sides of Belmont since the day she first met him, but despite everything, he could still surprise her."
    ""

# SailorPath10_c4e4cc5e (line 34648)
translate ru SailorPath10_c4e4cc5e:
    # "He played with them, taught them how to read the stars, and offered a more firm hand when Sarah's soft approach failed to keep their children in line."
    ""

# SailorPath10_ab1bab68 (line 34649)
translate ru SailorPath10_ab1bab68:
    # "With no more voyages out to sea, Sarah had her husband all to herself."
    ""

# SailorPath10_00a58a96 (line 34650)
translate ru SailorPath10_00a58a96:
    # "In little time at all, what had been three children soon became seven."
    ""

# SailorPath10_bf089ebf (line 34651)
translate ru SailorPath10_bf089ebf:
    # "The townsfolk grew to love Sarah and her large family."
    ""

# SailorPath10_c48cbb23 (line 34652)
translate ru SailorPath10_c48cbb23:
    # "Though they always remained wary of Belmont and his more coarse behavior, they eventually settled on trusting Sarah's judgement."
    ""

# SailorPath10_1b166dca (line 34653)
translate ru SailorPath10_1b166dca:
    # "If she decided he was good enough for her, who were any of them to think otherwise."
    ""

# SailorPath10_132dd395 (line 34654)
translate ru SailorPath10_132dd395:
    # "And so the years slipped by."
    ""

# SailorPath10_2dafff1f (line 34655)
translate ru SailorPath10_2dafff1f:
    # "She never bore him more than seven children, but seven proved plenty."
    ""

# SailorPath10_2a631129 (line 34656)
translate ru SailorPath10_2a631129:
    # "With each passing year, Sarah and her family grew ever more interwoven into the fabric of the small town of Northam."
    ""

# SailorPath10_080d1149 (line 34657)
translate ru SailorPath10_080d1149:
    # "Going to school, taking on trades, eventually forming families of their own."
    ""

# SailorPath10_38a31926 (line 34658)
translate ru SailorPath10_38a31926:
    # "On the edge of the world, where nothing of concern ever happened, Sarah watched her family grow old and found her hapiness."
    ""

# SailorPath10_9006cca7 (line 34659)
translate ru SailorPath10_9006cca7:
    # "This is how she lived."
    ""

# SailorPath10_26015050 (line 34660)
translate ru SailorPath10_26015050:
    # "So ends the story of Sarah Rose."
    ""

# SailorPath10_597c2257 (line 34661)
translate ru SailorPath10_597c2257:
    # "Princess. Sailor. Wife to Belmont."
    ""

# SailorPath10_9ec104ac (line 34662)
translate ru SailorPath10_9ec104ac:
    # "The End."
    ""

